76561198114472474,Recommended,263200,9023638,"Posted: 8 February, 2014",all,RussianSanta556,"Signs of Life is an excellent game. I can recommend it for several reasons, and those will be listed.It has a wide array of content, even if it is early access. I haven't played long, but I've already seen four fully (And beautifully) textured armor sets, as well as various different weapons and tools. There's a decent array of creatures, and more will hopefully be added. There is a good elemnt of exploration, even if the world is limited. Furthermore, the world is well designed and constructed. (There's a difference there)It has a... servicable survival element. If you die, you lose all your items and there are a multitude of ways to die. The qualms I have with it is how easy it is to gather food and kill monsters. The fighting is also simple, which is perfectly fine, and in this case, good.The game's controls are... Fine. You can rebind keys and all that, and the game is easy enough to figure out after awhile. However, there are a few minor problems with it. E.G. If you rebind a key, it goes back to default when you leave the game.The game has good textures and a decent aesthetic. However, if there was one qualm I had with it, it was the voxel-based terrain. Some games do well with it, but those games (Like minecraft) usually don't utilize good textures, they're trying to instill nostalgia. In my eyes, voxels and lifelike graphics don't match. Still, it's still only a minor qualm, and many people enjoy the voxels. I might just be the black sheep.Overall, I'd recommend this game for the above reasons. It has a great concept, it has great playability, it runs fine, and a fine aesthetic. Buy Signs of Life, it's well worth the price."
