76561198038046971,Recommended,263200,17279349,"Posted: 29 July, 2015",all,Tony [Actual Skeleton],"'Signs of life' is another one of 'dem ol' Sanbox games. But unlike most sandbox games, Signs of life has a lot more of a better feel to it, such as characters bending this way and that to look in the mouse's direction, pickaxes colliding with rock in it's swing arc regardless of whether or not that's the one you aim your cursor at, running and walking aminations are great, and all in all it brings a lot of life to the character. You're not some blocky dude, or a sprite that looks like it was ripped from Final fantasy, you play as a detailed human being.You begin your journey alone, save for your trusty wrist device's AI (Whom may or may not have zero sympathy for human life), aboard a pod freshly landed on some alien planet that isn't too different from earth, save for the fact that you can probably walk along it's surface in like, 15 minutes. But you aren't quite so alone, with sheep, tapirs, and other generally peaceful wildlife decorating the planet's surface, while deep underground, you'll find things that you'll need to shake more than just a stick at.With plenty of weapons, armors, parts, items, objects, and basically a whole metric sh-tton of other stuff, this game is packed with crafting materials. And you don't just use some logs to make things like a chair. No, you saw them into planks, use cotton and thread to make padding, and craft nails that you require a hammer to use to assamble the entire thing. Crafting isn't just slapping a few pieces together, you craft all of the parts needed to assemble what you need. And there's lots of things to be made. Need guns? SMGs, handguns, shotguns, rifles and more are a lengthy mining trip away. Want to hit things? Swords, clubs, bats, and even weapons made from pieces of your foes can be made to give your target a good beating or cut them down to size. Want to protect your delicate babyflesh? Armors can be made out of anything, from wood and twine, to bone, to iron, to silver, to some of the rarest minerals you can find.The game is still in alpha when this review is/was made, but it's still a fantastic game so far, with multiplayer now built in and more amazing things on the way. Keep it up, developers, this one may just set a trend for a whole new generation of sandbox games."
