,Recommended,263200,12395807,"Posted: 6 October, 2014",all,Populix,"Signs of life. The title of the game explains exactly what this game injects into the Open World/ Survial/ Building hybrid genre thing that a good few games have going on. A pulse in the almost ""Beating a dead horse"" game style. A sign of life that is! Puns aside. I don't compare games. Signs of Life lands you on an alien planet, that isn't too alien. It's like Earth in ways, thats why it was chosen. But like Earth it's got it's own life forms and plant life. This of course means some will be harmless and others want your sweet meats! Gravity is still a thing here, but your guy jumps like it may be less, or he might just be robot from the waist down, I don't know IT'S SPACE AGE FUTURE STUFF!Onto the game itself. There's a story, but it's being worked on of course. The crafting is pretty solid, a component you might need to craft makes sense. One thing about it, is you're gonna need to take steps at times. Take Dynamite sticks for example, you need cotton and wood to make a spool of cotton fabric, then you need the fabric AND more cotton to make cotton cushoining. But that's still only 1 out of 4 items you need to make Dynamite. This isn't really a problem with how much the game provides you with! Sure you think it has too many things around, but you're also on an Alien planet that hasn't been overrun by humanity so supplies abundant! And you're gonna notice you wished you collected more before trying to craft, trust me.This is a good game. I can see it going in a good direction and the scale being wonderous. Buy it for a breath of fresh air."
