,Recommended,263200,34137902,Posted: 9 August,all,Kavrick,"First of all, i'd only recommend this if you dont mind steep learning curve. I'm gonna start off with the bad stuff and the glaringly obvious first problem is that the game gives you very very little direction. Although i kinda like being left to my own devices, it feels like a lot of basic things you need are pretty hard to find, mining traditionally just simply isn't worth it, as the stuff you really need isn't easy to find just by mining tiles, your best bet is smashing diposits you find in caves, which is kinda tedious to go around and find them. The second huge problem this game suffers from is the UI is terrible, it looks nice, i like all the bags and how they sort themselves depending on what kinda bag they are, but the items are so small that it's hard to find what you're looking for.Now i'll go on to the good parts, the biggest thing i love about this game might be weird, but i love how great this game controls, all the movement and animations are really smooth and just feel great. And to go along with this game having a steep learning curve, it has tons of stuff in it, loads of stuff to craft and read, but of course this also means that the amount of stuff is kinda overwehlming, there's a lot of stuff with no direction.Overall, this game plays great and has a lot of content, although you can go through the content rather fast and the dev team seems to be rather slow with how fast they make content for the game. Fighting is pretty basic in this game but it's far from clunky, i feel like melee weapons are just way stronger than ranged, i understand that this is for balance, but running up and hitting them with your sword is way less hastle than crafting tons of ammo and slowely chipping away at enemies, as ranged weapons seem to do less than half the damage of melee.As for if i'd recommend this, if you love crafting games, i would recommend this, it's a good time sink for just running around fighting, building and mining, the crafting can be a bit tedious with certain recipies needing a lot of small and rather trivial items which seems kinda unneccessary but overall i'd say it's a good game."
