,Recommended,263200,17373283,"Posted: 3 August, 2015",all,Lotevenstar,"This game has a curious quaint style that starts to draw you in.   The crafting is fun and interesting,  showing promise at release as long as more content is added,  as crafting is currently a bit limited.   Ingesting ideas abound,  but again need a little more polish,  as enemy ai is easily tricked,  and is even simpler on multiplayer. The current final boss of the game is challenging on single player,  but doesn't drop aggro on the primary target, allowing a friend to stand behind it jabbing away. I really enjoyed the experience,  being a bit slower than similar titles wasn't a detriment,  and can't wait to see where the development takes this game.   Optimistically 8.5/10 for future game, current version 6/10 for small content/unfinished and low challenge through the material placement system."
